    <text type="letter">
        <body>     
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.00429_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                    <name type="place">Marion Thrasher, A. M., <lb/> SUPERINTENDENT <lb/>OF</name>
                    <name type="place">EDGAR PUBLIC SCHOOLS.</name>
                    <date when="1885-12-06">Edgar, Neb. <handShift rend="manuscript"/>Dec 6th
                        <handShift rend="printed"/><handShift rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>5<ptr target="loc.04269_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Mr Walt Whitman</salute>
                <salute>My Dear Old Friend.</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> For years, I have known you intimately, through your poems. The people of the "Great
                West" would like to see you&#8212;as they cannot come to you, could we not persuade
                you to come to them? </p>
            <p> Am known extensively over our State&#8212;as a lecturer before "Teachers
                Associations," and can arrange for you to give ten readings of your poems, in ten of
                our largest cities (you, East, would call them towns) at $50 for night&#8212;total
                $500.00&#8212;your expenses need not be more than $100, to and from your home
                here&#8212;netting you $400 for a fortnights work. You will confer the greatest
                favor on your many Western friends by accepting. If the Winter be too severe; could
                you come in the Spring&#8212;say, May? Trusting to hear favorably from you&#8212;I am&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely yours</salute>
                <signed>Marion Thrasher</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Will furnish you the highest references.</p>
            </postscript>
